hat socio-technical resources are key factors in understanding migration flows and migrant-home relations. Overall, this book provides rare insights into the rural side of migration and farmers' knowledge and agency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAgricultural innovationszChina. 0aRice farmingzChina. 0aRural-urban migrationzChina. 4aAgriculture and farming. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aChina. 4aDevelopment Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aMigration, immigration and emigration. 4aPopulation and migration geography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aChina, rural-urban migration, knowledge and skill, rice farming, migrant-left-behind nexus.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048552184zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048552184zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048552184/original  a978-3-11-074322-7 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b202